SvgArc, SvgLine, SvgPolyLine
public abstract class SvgDoubleEndedGraphicElement
extends SvgGraphicElement

This abstract class is the super class for all elements that have a start and end point. The methods in this class allow for query of the start and end point and the comparison of the locality of the points. With this information it is possible to determine if elements share the same start or end point and therefore are really one contiguous group like a wire run.

Version:
0.01 - June 23, 2003

getEndPoint

public Point getEndPoint()
Returns the end point of the object. The end point is the opposite of anchor point.

getStartPoint

public Point getStartPoint()
Returns the start point of a double ended graphic object (which is the Anchor). It is a trivial implementation that duplicates another method but this method will help keep the abstraction clear to the author's intent.

Returns:
Point The anchor point or point of origin for the object.

getAllSegmentPoints

public void getAllSegmentPoints(java.util.Vector points)
This method returns the end points of all the segments in this object. For SvgLine and the like the method populates the argument vector with the start and end points, but for SvgPolyLine the entire set of intersection points is returned (as references). The method does not alter the contents of the argument vector, but simply adds the points to the end. Start point is added first, end point second.

Parameters:
points - A vector for storing the points. If the vector is null the method returns; it is upto the caller to manage this.

shareStartOrEndPoint

public boolean shareStartOrEndPoint(SvgDoubleEndedGraphicElement sp)
This method compares two SvgDoubleEndedGraphicElements and determines whether either the start OR end point are local to each other. If two points are local they are said to be on the same point +- the fuzz value.

If the start point are located on the same spot the method exits with a true value and does not check the end point.
